<TEXT>
<P>
'Monday Night Live' Downtown-Bound: Those infamous star-studded Monday night 
jam sessions at the China Club in Hollywood are no more. 
</P>
<P>
The house band for the jams, Jim Ehinger and the Nasty Survivors, has moved its 
base to Vertigo in downtown Los Angeles. While not specifically knocking the 
accommodations at the China Club, band publicists said that the move will 
provide "musicians and guests easier access, a larger room in which to listen 
and play" and "a courteous approach at the front door." They added that the 
sound and light system at Vertigo was superior to the China Club. Elton John 
and Sting have played in previous China Club jams. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
