<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old Long Beach youth was "an accident waiting to happen" from 
emotional problems caused by the murder of his sister, a psychiatrist testified 
Monday at a hearing to determine whether the teen-ager will be tried as a 
juvenile or as an adult for shooting two deaf brothers, one fatally. 
</P>
<P>
