<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: BENTON CO. BUYS INTEREST IN LOUISIANA OIL FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Benton Oil and Gas Co. of Ventura said it acquired working interests in the 
West Cote Blanche Bay Field, located in shallow water off the coast of southern 
Louisiana. 
</P>
<P>
The oil and gas exploration and production company said it acquired a 5.47% 
interest in the field for about $2.1 million from a group of independent oil 
and gas companies and signed an agreement to purchase another 16.47% interest 
for $6.5 million from the same group. 
</P>
<P>
The West Cote Blanche Bay Field was discovered in 1938 and has produced about 
200 million barrels of oil, Benton said. It estimated that existing reserves 
could be up to 3 million barrels. 
</P>
