<TEXT>
<P>
The five permanent members of the U.N. Security Council are to meet in the 
French capital Monday in another effort to end the 10-year-old Cambodian civil 
war. 
</P>
<P>
It will be the first such attempt since three of the four feuding Cambodian 
factions signed an agreement in Tokyo last month calling for a cease-fire and 
establishment of a de facto temporary government prior to free elections. 
</P>
<P>
But the warring factions still can't agree on fundamental issues and are to be 
excluded from the Paris meeting. 
