<TEXT>
<P>
The owner of a Radio Shack electronics store was ordered today to stand trial 
for secretly videotaping three teen-age employees having sex with their 
boyfriends in the store after hours. 
</P>
<P>
The three former part-time employees told Allegan District Judge Harry Beach 
that their boss, Howard DeYoung, gave them keys to the store and told them they 
were free to use the television room any time after closing. 
</P>
<P>
Beach bound DeYoung, 38, over for trial after rejecting defense lawyer Larry 
Woods' claim there was no evidence to suggest the tapes were made for 
commercial purposes. 
</P>
<P>
The three young women were asked to identify who appeared on the tapes and when 
they might have been made. All three said they had no idea they were being 
taped and that DeYoung had told them a security camera in the room could be 
turned off. 
